	<title>Reports</title>
	<section id="Reports_ScheduleChart">
		<indexterm>
			<primary>Reports</primary>
			<secondary>Schedule Chart</secondary>
		</indexterm>
	<?dbeclipse ctx_description="The schedule chart provides a visual representation of the schedule. Each row represents a vessel showing the sequence of cargoes, drydocks, charter outs and other events in time." ?>
		<title>Schedule Chart</title>
		<para>The schedule chart provides a visual representation of the schedule. Each row represents a vessel showing the sequence of cargoes, drydocks, charter
			outs and other events in time.
		</para>
		<para>Selecting an element in the view will cause the other reports and editor to &quot;snap&quot; to that element if possible. For example selecting a load
			or discharge event will cause the relevant cargo to be highlighted in the cargo report. Additionally, the properties view will show additional details about
			the event. A summary will be shown in the tooltip which is displayed when hovering over an event.
		</para>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem>
				<para>Also known as the Gantt view</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Vessel names also include scenario name when multiple
					scenarios are selected.
				</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>FOB / DES cargoes in single row.</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Colour Scheme (show examples in screenshots)</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Sort Modes (multiple scenarios)</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Multiple Scenarios: stack</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Pin/Diff: No change over multiple scenarios</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</section>
	<section id="Reports_PortRotationReportView">
